# Day 13 - Minimum Sideway Jumps (Dynamic Programming)

This repository contains solutions to the LeetCode problem:

## Problem
**1824. Minimum Sideway Jumps**

A frog starts on lane 2 at point 0 and wants to reach point n while avoiding obstacles.

The objective is to find the minimum number of side jumps required.

---

## Approaches Covered

### 1. Recursive Solution
- Pure recursion
- Exponential Time Complexity

### 2. Memoization (Top-Down DP)
- Stores computed states
- Time Complexity: O(N × 3)

### 3. Tabulation (Bottom-Up DP)
- Iterative DP
- Time Complexity: O(N × 3)

### 4. Space Optimized DP
- Uses only two arrays
- Time Complexity: O(N × 3)
- Space Complexity: O(3)

---

## Complexity

| Approach | Time | Space |
|----------|------|-------|
| Recursion | Exponential | O(N) |
